* PHP names the variable, $color, by the same name assigned to the radio button and assigns to the variable the value that was selected by the user when he or she clicked the button. If the user clicked red, then $color will evaluate to red.
* The default statement is not necessary, but is good practice in case you should decide to replace the default with an additional case label later on.

